ont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'>21 day eval at: <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.intellij.com/\">http://www.intellij.com</a> (Nuff said except to\nsay I ain&#8217;t associated with these guys in any way except being delighted by\ntheir product). </span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'>Now back to our regularly scheduled\nprogramming.</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'>Richard </span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<div style='border:none;border-left:solid blue 1.5pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 4.0pt;'>\n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Tahoma;'>-----Original Message-----<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>From:</span></b> Robertson, Don\n[mailto:don.robertson@...] <br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>Sent:</span></b> Wednesday, January 09, 2002\n12:41 PM<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>To:</span></b> &#39;junit@yahoogroups.com&#39;<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>Subject:</span></b> RE: [junit] Simple\nconceptual question when changing accessors of a method ...</span></font></p>\n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='\nfont-size:12.0pt;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>If it&#39;s\n&quot;Refactoring&quot; that you&#39;re considering buying and reading, go ahead -\nit&#39;s well worth your time. It&#39;s one of those rare books that can fundamentally\nchange the way you think about programming.</span></font></p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Don</span></font>\n</p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>-----Original\nMessage-----</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>From: Thomas SMETS [<a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:tsmets@...\">mailto:tsmets@...</a>]</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Sent: Wednesday, January 09, 2002\n7:37 AM</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>To: junit@yahoogroups.com</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Subject: Re: [junit] Simple\nconceptual question when changing accessors</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>of a method ...</span></font> </p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='\nfont-size:12.0pt;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Hi Jason,</span></font>\n</p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Sounds\nfine to me...</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Just feel there&#39;s yet another book\nI should buy (the easy part)</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&amp; read (that&#39;s harder to find\nthe time for).</span></font> </p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Much tx,</span></font>\n</p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Thomas,</span></font>\n</p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='\nfont-size:12.0pt;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>--</span></font>\n</p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Thomas\nSMETS - Certified Java Programmer</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>rue J. Wytsmanstraat 62</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>1050 Brussel - Bruxelles</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Tel : +32 (0)2 742. 05. 94.</span></font>\n</p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\" style='margin-bottom:12.0pt;'><font size=\"3\"\n face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:12.0pt;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>-----\nOriginal Message -----</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>From: &quot;Jason Rogers&quot;\n&lt;jacaetev@...&gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>To: &lt;junit@yahoogroups.com&gt;</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Sent: Wednesday, January 09, 2002\n3:30 PM</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Subject: Re: [junit] Simple\nconceptual question when changing accessors of a</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>method ...</span></font> </p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-133616690MsoNormal\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='\nfont-size:12.0pt;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; What\nabout another approach...</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; Move those currently public\nmethods out to another class where they remain</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; public, create a fixtue for\nthat object, then move the test code to the</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>new</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; fixture.&nbsp; Have the\noriginal object reference the new object for that</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; functionality.&nbsp;\n&lt;Extract Class and Move Field from Fowler&#39;s &quot;Refactoring&quot;&gt;</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; -jason</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; --- Thomas SMETS\n&lt;tsmets@...&gt; wrote:</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; Hi All,</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I\nwanna say that I&#39;ve been reviewing the archives</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nbefore being mail bombed</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\non &quot;private &amp; inner&quot; references.</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; I&#39;ve been working on my\ncertif. assignement lately &amp; have been</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>confronted to</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; the following problem.</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; I&#39;ve the &quot;Flight by\nNight Cpy&quot; to upgrade. The DB is now well enhenced &amp;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; contains a flush on close\nso the deleted records a re definitively</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>removed,</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; etc...</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; Everything has been done\nin the almost purest JUnit style (must admit</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>many</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; coding followed by\ntesting, but there&#39;s none piping over my schoulder,</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>so</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; ;-) ).</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; I&#39;d like now to change\nthe accessor of some methods from public to</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; &quot;friendly&quot; or\nprotected for some methods as they are not needed for the</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; caller anymore.</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; My question is twofold :</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n1°. What are the possibilities ?</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nWould simply moving the TestCase as inner</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt;\n<blockquote><span title=\"ireply\"> &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; class suite the matter.</span></blockquote></span></font>\n<br>\n <font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n2°. Am I&#39;m better to make all the TestCases member</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt;\n<blockquote><span title=\"ireply\"> &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; of the package of the\n </span></blockquote>class to test &amp; make the accessor</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt;\n<blockquote><span title=\"ireply\"> &gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; protected ?</span></blockquote></span></font> <br>\n <font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; Tx for advice,</span></font>\n<br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; Thomas,</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt;</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; p.s. :</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; To read with a sens of\nhumour</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; I was wandering if some\nof the fossiles wagging around this web site</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>could</span></font> <br>\n<font size=\"2\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>&gt; &gt; lay down s